      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p><rs type="material" key="marmor">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">panel</rs>, broken below (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.44</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.21</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.03</measure>).</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Poor and unevenly aligned, av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02</measure>; from l. 7 the lightly scratched draft
which the cutter often failed to follow at all exactly can be seen at
many points, enabling us to correct some errors. Cursive forms. In ll.
2 and 4 the crossbar of <term>epsilon</term> is omitted. <foreign lang="grc">ΚΕ</foreign> in l.12.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0401" notAfter="0600">Fifth/sixth century</date> or later (<rs type="criteria">content</rs>, <rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
        <ab>
		  		<lb n="1"/><g type="cross"/> <w lemma="ἔνθα">ἔνθα</w> <w lemma="κατάκειμαι">κα<lb n="2" type="worddiv"/>τάκιτε</w><lb n="3"/><persName key="eutychia1" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Εὐτυχία">Εὐτυχία</name></persName><lb n="4"/><w lemma="γίγνομαι">γεναμ<unclear reason="damage">έ</unclear><lb n="5" type="worddiv"/>νι</w> <w lemma="τρέφω">θρέψα<lb n="6" type="worddiv"/>σα</w> <w lemma="καί">κὲ</w> <w lemma="εὐπρεπής">εὐπρε<lb n="7" type="worddiv"/>πὲς</w> <w lemma="μετά">με<lb n="8" type="worddiv"/>τὰ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶν</w> <w lemma="πέδιον">πε<lb n="9" type="worddiv"/>δίων</w> <w lemma="αὐτός">αὐ<lb n="10" type="worddiv"/>τῆς</w>· <persName key="Lord" type="divine" full="yes"><w lemma="κύριος">Κύριε</w></persName><lb n="11"/><w lemma="μνάομαι">μνήσθιθι</w><lb n="12"/><w lemma="αὐτός">αὐτῆς</w> <persName key="Lord" type="divine" full="yes"><w lemma="κύριος"><expan><abbr>Κ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ύρι</supplied><abbr>ε</abbr></expan></w></persName>.</ab> 
      </div>

      <div type="apparatus">
        <head>Apparatus</head>
        <p>l. 6. Misprinted as <foreign lang="grc">εὐπε</foreign>- in <title level="m">ALA</title>.</p>
        <p>l. 10. Draft as given, but the mason only cut <foreign lang="grc">ΚΥΙΕ</foreign>.</p>
        <p>l. 12. Draft as given, but the mason cut <foreign lang="grc">Υ<space extent="1" unit="character" dim="horizontal"/>ΤΗΣ</foreign>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>Here lies Eutychia. who was <seg cert="low">a mother/nurse</seg>, and of good
repute, with her children. Lord remember her, Lord.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="IX.44">IX.44</xref>.</p>
      </div>

